01:40:43,954 --> 01:40:46,998
WELLS: l felt a lot ofaffection
for the characters in this movie.

1670
01:40:47,499 --> 01:40:50,084
And this is
an admittedly traditional wrap-up

1671
01:40:50,169 --> 01:40:51,919
going on at this wedding reception.

1672
01:40:52,463 --> 01:40:54,422
We are getting a lot of final glimpses

1673
01:40:54,506 --> 01:40:56,883
of characters
that we came to care about.

1674
01:40:59,636 --> 01:41:01,596
Visually, we designed
the wedding reception

1675
01:41:01,680 --> 01:41:05,308
around white and yellow,
the colors of the lemons and wisteria.

1676
01:41:05,434 --> 01:41:07,185
And it feels like
the garden and the house

1677
01:41:07,269 --> 01:41:09,604
have finally arrived at their full fruition.

1678
01:41:10,689 --> 01:41:11,981
Mamma!

1679
01:41:16,820 --> 01:41:18,780
(GUESTS CHANT)
Bacio! Bacio! Bacio! Bacio!

1680
01:41:19,990 --> 01:41:22,575
WELLS: There is an undeniable
sweetness to this scene,

1681
01:41:22,659 --> 01:41:26,871
particularly when Frances
sees her old friend, Signor Martini.

1682
01:41:28,999 --> 01:41:30,875
He looks like a groom standing there

1683
01:41:30,959 --> 01:41:33,336
waiting for her to walk down the aisle
to meet him.

1684
01:41:33,962 --> 01:41:35,963
What are you thinking?

1685
01:41:37,341 --> 01:41:39,592
WELLS: Their friendship is one
of my favorite things in the movie.

1686
01:41:39,676 --> 01:41:40,718
It's been earned.

1687
01:41:40,803 --> 01:41:44,138
And when he points out
that her wishes have been granted,

1688
01:41:44,223 --> 01:41:46,974
there is a sweet melancholy feeling
of arrival to that

1689
01:41:47,059 --> 01:41:48,643
that reminds me
of the kind of resolution

1690
01:41:48,727 --> 01:41:50,186
you find in an O. Henry story.

1691
01:42:00,531 --> 01:42:02,115
Yeah.

1692
01:42:02,199 --> 01:42:05,201
And you said you wanted
there to be a family here.

1693
01:42:12,292 --> 01:42:14,293
You're right.

1694
01:42:15,212 --> 01:42:17,463
I got my wish.

1695
01:42:18,340 --> 01:42:20,383
WELLS: l love Diane's performance
as she realizes

1696
01:42:20,467 --> 01:42:22,927
that she has, indeed,
gotten everything she's asked for.

1697
01:42:23,387 --> 01:42:26,055
She seems stunned
and sort of quietly amazed.

1698
01:42:45,075 --> 01:42:46,409
ln the book Under the Tuscan Sun,

1699
01:42:47,119 --> 01:42:49,078
Frances Mayes is married to Ed Mayes

1700
01:42:49,163 --> 01:42:52,373
and she writes about him
on almost every page of her memoir.

1701
01:42:54,042 --> 01:42:57,253
I thought it was important
for my adaptation

1702
01:42:57,337 --> 01:43:00,506
that I bring Ed Mayes
into the story somewhere

1703
01:43:00,591 --> 01:43:03,092
and here he is,
played by David Sutcliffe.

1704
01:43:06,763 --> 01:43:10,433
But in my mind, I didn't think
she necessarily ended up with this guy.

1705
01:43:10,601 --> 01:43:13,352
I didn't put her in a wedding dress.
I didn't get her pregnant,

1706
01:43:13,437 --> 01:43:15,771
which would've been a denial
of what came before.

1707
01:43:16,148 --> 01:43:17,231
I just wanted to show that

1708
01:43:17,316 --> 01:43:20,526
once she had achieved a sense
of completion on her own,

1709
01:43:20,611 --> 01:43:23,321
and once she realized that she, indeed,

1710
01:43:23,405 --> 01:43:25,156
already had everything she needed,

1711
01:43:25,240 --> 01:43:27,909
that then she was open
for more good things to come her way.

1712
01:43:29,494 --> 01:43:31,037
No, no.

1713
01:43:31,121 --> 01:43:36,626
Don't worry. It was by far the very best
bad review I've ever received.

1714
01:43:36,710 --> 01:43:38,628
-You're kidding.
-I'm not.

1715
01:43:38,712 --> 01:43:41,672
It helped me get to my next book.

1716
01:43:42,257 --> 01:43:45,218
Anyway, I've been traveling
around Tuscany.

1717
01:43:46,178 --> 01:43:48,721
Someone said that you lived up here,
and...

1718
01:43:51,391 --> 01:43:54,393
WELLS: Eversince l became
a screenwriter 15 years ago,

1719
01:43:54,811 --> 01:43:59,106
I've been warned and admonished
about too many endings on movies.

1720
01:43:59,983 --> 01:44:03,361
And I think that this movie
may have more endings

1721
01:44:03,445 --> 01:44:06,364
than any movie
I've ever seen in my life.

1722
01:44:06,448 --> 01:44:10,743
But it works for me. It feels like
all the dominoes were lined up.

1723
01:44:11,078 --> 01:44:13,371
Now I flick the first one with my finger

1724
01:44:13,455 --> 01:44:16,916
and they all start to fall
with satisfying clacks.

1725
01:44:26,343 --> 01:44:27,885
FRANCES: They say they built
the train tracks

1726
01:44:27,970 --> 01:44:30,096
over the Alps
between Vienna and Venice

1727
01:44:30,180 --> 01:44:33,391
before there was a train
that could make the trip.

1728
01:44:33,475 --> 01:44:35,309
They built it anyway.

1729
01:44:35,394 --> 01:44:38,604
They knew one day
the train would come.

1730
01:44:40,232 --> 01:44:42,900
Any arbitrary turning along the way,

1731
01:44:42,985 --> 01:44:47,154
and l would be elsewhere,
I would be different.

1732
01:44:48,865 --> 01:44:53,202
What are four walls, anyway?
They are what they contain.

1733
01:44:53,328 --> 01:44:55,955
The house protects the dreamer.

1734
01:44:56,039 --> 01:45:00,584
Unthinkably good things can happen,
even late in the game.

1735
01:45:00,711 --> 01:45:03,004
It's such a surprise.

1736
01:45:08,010 --> 01:45:11,304
WELLS: There is an inevitability
to what happens in this scene.

1737
01:45:11,555 --> 01:45:16,225
But I've always felt that unpredictability
is an overrated virtue in movies.

1738
01:45:16,476 --> 01:45:20,521
Especially in romantic comedies
or human comedies like this one,

1739
01:45:20,605 --> 01:45:22,732
unpredictability isn't really
part of the genre.

1740
01:45:23,191 --> 01:45:24,817
We know we are headed
for a happy ending.

1741
01:45:24,901 --> 01:45:28,070
And we want to go there.
Of course, the ending is predictable.

1742
01:45:28,155 --> 01:45:30,906
It's not the fact that it happens

1743
01:45:30,991 --> 01:45:33,326
that's supposed to be
the source of pleasure.

1744
01:45:33,410 --> 01:45:37,830
It's how it happens and how the actors,
how the characters react

1745
01:45:37,914 --> 01:45:39,749
and the impact that it has upon them.

1746
